lus extra  funding  notable events  violence against staff  client fraud  staff fraud  treatment injury claims  bronwyn pullar privacy breach  see also  references  external links featuresedit acc is the sole and compulsory provider of accident insurance in new zealand for all work and nonwork injuries the corporation administers the acc scheme on a nofault basis so that anyone – regardless of the way in which they incurred an injury – has coverage under the scheme due to the schemes nofault basis people who have suffered personal injury do not have the right to sue an atfault party except for exemplary damages the acc scheme provides a range of entitlements to injured people however  percent of new claims in – were for treatment costs only other entitlements include weekly compensation for lost earnings paid at a rate of  of a persons preinjury earnings and the cost of home or vehicle modifications for the seriously injured the scheme offers entitlements subject to various eligibility criteria acc works with trusted partners and communities to prevent injuries these initiatives include but are not limited to rugbysmart with new zealand rugby ride forever mates and dates and ‘make your home a safety zone’ with safekids historyedit acc has its origins in the  workers compensation act workers compensation for accidents act  which established a limited compensation scheme for workers who had suffered injuries where there was no directly responsible party in  a new zealand royal commission chaired by high court judge owen woodhouse recommended extending this compensation to cover all injuries on a nofault basis following this report on  april  the new zealand government established the accident compensation commission to implement the requirements of the  accident compensation act and the  amendments the act was later replaced by the injury prevention rehabilitation and compensation act  which was renamed the accident compensation act  in  the annual report  of the accident compensation commission proposed that the distinction between accidents which are covered and illness which is not should be dropped but this proposal was not taken up by the government in  the government renamed the accident compensation commission as the accident compensation corporation from  july  the fourth national government allowed private insurance operators to provide workrelated accident insurance and acc was briefly exposed to competition the fifth labour government elected in november  repealed this change and as of  july  reinstated the acc as the sole provider of accident insurance coverage administration of leviesedit acc is primarily funded through a combination of levies and government contributions income collected from each source goes into predetermined account based on the source costs relating to an injury are paid from one of these accounts based on the type and cause of the injury the four main accounts are work earners nonearners and motor vehicle there is also a fifth account treatment injury formerly medical misadventure that draws on both the earners and nonearners account account covers income sources work workrelated injuries levies collected from employers and selfemployed people the amount payable averages  of an employers payroll or income earned as of  april  rates vary depending on the employers industry and risks associated with it earners nonwork injuries by income earners levies collected in conjunction with tax deductions on income paid by employees through paye or by selfemployed people directly the amount payable is  of income earned as of  april  nonearners nonwork injuries by nonincome earners eg children elderly unemployed visitors government contribution from the general taxation pool motor vehicle injuries relating to motor vehicles on public roads levies included in the price of petrol not diesel or lpg and through motor vehicle license fees levies average  gst exclusive per vehicle per year as of july  with motorcycles and heavy vehicles paying more than average due to the increased likelihood of injury associated with these modes of transport the petrol levy set at c per litre gst exclusive treatment injury injuries as a result of medical treatment funded from the earners and nonearners accounts depending on the clients employment status acc for the selfemployed – acc coverplus extraedit acc coverplus extra was introduced by acc to provide cover for selfemployed workers and business owners that would fail to otherwise be covered adequately by the standard acc cover plus policy it works by paying an agreed level of compensation in the event of an injury resulting in time off from work with this cover already agreed upon any business would not have to prove loss of income and has certainty on their amount of cover in the event of an accident injury acc cover plus policy was designed to cover employees and would only pay  of the net taxable income with acc cover plus extra a selfemployed contractor would get  of the preagreed compensation cover until one was fit for fulltime work a business owner would be able to get compensation under acc cover plus extra even if the business continued to earn income whilst the business owner was off work injured this would not be possible with the standard policy fundingedit acc offices in palmerston north acc initially had a payasyougo funding model which collected only enough levies during the year to cover the cost of claims for that particular year in  a fully funded model was adopted whereby sufficient levies were collected to cover the lifetime cost of each injury – which might require compensation over a period of  years or more however getting acc onto a strong financial footing was not easy and in  acc posted a  billion loss – described as the biggest corporate loss in new zealands history this cost escalation is thought to have been due to an increase in the number of claims a widening of entitlements and increased costs of meeting the claims another factor was physiotherapy services being made free at the point of delivery leading to overservicing of clients between  and  this appears to have contributed to an increase in physiotherapy costs of  the  reimbursement scheme for physiotherapist services was ended and acc levies on wages and motorists were increased acc chairman john judge told the sunday startimes that it was going to take a hardnosed approach to get acc into a sustainable position this would require substantial levy increases and legislative change to get people off the scheme and back to work quicker by  acc had made good progress towards its goal of being fully funded and was  billion short of matching liabilities b with its assets b towards the end of  acc minister judith collins announced that government would not cut acc levies for the – year while the acc board and ministry of business innovation and employment had recommended reducing the levies by between  and  per cent collins stated that the governments decision was motivated by the uncertain economic conditions and a desire to ensure that reductions to the levy were sustainable andrew little the labour partys acc spokesman criticised this decision claiming that it was driven by the governments attempt to bring the budget into surplus and reducing the levy would provide a boost to the economy in the  budget collins announced a  billion cut in acc levies over the next two years collins said the earners and workers accounts were now fully funded after the corporation reduced the number of long term acc claimants from  to less than  in  acc’s outstanding claims liability ocl increased by  billion which lead to a net deficit of  billion the ocl measures the future cost of all existing acc claims that year also saw  million claims accepted a  increase from the previous year  billion was paid out to all new and existing claims there has been some conjecture over whether or not acc staff were paid incentives to remove long term clients off weekly compensation this was refuted by exceo ralph stewart in  that year there were  longterm claimants registered with acc – down by over  notable eventsedit violence against staffedit in some cases acc clients have threatened or attempted to harm acc staff members in  a staff member was fatally stabbed by a claimant at an acc office in henderson in  acc logos were removed from company vehicles after several staff were rammed or driven off the road by other drivers the following year a threat against former chief executive ralph stewart led to a decision for security staff to be posted outside his home there have been at least two threats to blow up a car bomb outside acc offices and police have had to be called on several other occasions in  there were a total of  recorded threats made against staff  the majority against case managers making difficult decisions on clients cases client fraudedit in  it was reported that  people have been convicted of defrauding acc of a total of more than  million over the past four years this includes clients claiming they were injured but who kept working while receiving acc benefits and medical practitioners who billed acc for more treatment than they actually provided another category of acc fraudster includes widows who continued claiming payments after their injured partners have subsequently died sometimes these payments went on for nearly  years before the fraud came to light – with one woman receiving nearly  after her husband had died staff fraudedit there have been a number of cases where acc staff have defrauded the corporation jeffrey chapman former acc chief executive from  to  was imprisoned for defrauding acc and other government agencies gavin robbins his successor from  to  was also charged with fraud but was acquitted in  a senior manager was convicted of dishonesty offences involving property leased to acc by private business interests in late  jonathan wright an acccontracted medical assessor was convicted of dishonestly obtaining over  in falsified travel expenses from acc treatment injury claimsedit medical misadventure claims were relabelled as treatment injury claims ti in  a treatment injury is when an injury is caused by treatment provided by a registered health professional these injuries are not a necessary part or ordinary consequence of the treatment bronwyn pullar privacy breachedit acc has had a number of breaches of privacy relating to claimants the most significant occurred in  after the release of details of  claimants to an acc claimant bronwyn pullar pullar had been battling acc since suffering a head injury in —and had  separate complaints against the agency—only one of which was about the privacy breaches in  she and former national party president michelle boag had a meeting with two senior acc managers to discuss her concerns acc referred the matter to the police claiming pullar had threatened to go to the media about the privacy breaches if she didnt get what she wanted the police listened to a tape recording of the meeting and decided there was no case to answer in march  acc minister nick smith resigned from cabinet after it was revealed that he had written letters on behalf of pullar who was a personal friend of his while he was acc minister acc chairman john judge continued to insist his version of events was correct and as a result acc minister judith collins did not renew his tenure on the acc board the chief executive of acc ralph stewart also resigned the next day three other board members – murray hilder rob campbell and john mccliskie – also resigned the fallout from the affair continued in may  when collins sued labour mps trevor mallard and andrew little for defamation over comments they made on radio new zealand broadcasts linking her to the leak of an email from michelle boag following the release of the files the case was settled after a high court hearing in november  an independent review of acc was conducted towards the end of  and found the organisation lacked a comprehensive strategy for protecting and managing claimants information and said acc had an almost cavalier attitude toward its clients the review showed that the culture within acc enabled its staff to target clients involved in privacy breaches and complaints rather than demonstrating respect for claimants in  a training academy for staff was mooted with an emphasis on a clientcentred approach see alsoedit tort reform atiyahs accidents referencesedit  accident compensation act   new zealand legislation parliamentary counsel office   see donselaar v donselaar   nzlr  confirmed by auckland city council v blundell   nzlr   nz rugby foundation  rugby smart wwwsportyconz retrieved    about » ride forever retrieved    preventing sexual violence wwwaccconz retrieved    make your home a safety zone wwwsafekidsnz retrieved    annual report  of the accident compensation commission p  see fenton v thorley  wn  for an old definition  a b how were funded  acc retrieved  may    current year’s levy rates acc  august  retrieved  february    a b types of cover for selfemployed wwwaccconz retrieved    a b the painful bills about to wallop your wallet  physiotherapy claims summary  acc moves to curtail rise in physiotherapy costs archived february   at the wayback machine  armstrong grahame  october  the painful bills about to wallop your wallet the sunday star times retrieved  may  dead link  funding issue brews in accs cauldron  govt ignored ministry call to trim acc levies by m  acc leads good economic news at national party convention nz herald  may   accs outstanding claims liability wwwaccconz retrieved    exboss defends acc rehabilitation policy    acc staff in line of fire  acc frauds hit m over past four years  don rennie administering accident compensation in the s   vuwlr    former acc property boss escapes jail over bribe  acc fraud doctor named in court  injuries and conditions covered by acc  community law community la