istory this cost escalation is thought to have been due to an increase in the number of claims a widening of entitlements and increased costs of meeting the claims another factor was physiotherapy services being made free at the point of delivery leading to overservicing of clients between  and  this appears to have contributed to an increase in physiotherapy costs of  the  reimbursement scheme for physiotherapist services was ended and acc levies on wages and motorists were increased acc chairman john judge told the sunday startimes that it was going to take a hardnosed approach to get acc into a sustainable position this would require substantial levy increases and legislative change to get people off the scheme and back to work quicker by  acc had made good progress towards its goal of being fully funded and was  billion short of matching liabilities b with its assets b towards the end of  acc minister judith collins announced that government would not cut acc levies for the – year while the acc board and ministry of business innovation and employment had recommended reducing the levies by between  and  per cent collins stated that the governments decision was motivated by the uncertain economic conditions and a desire to ensure that reductions to the levy were sustainable andrew little the labour partys acc spokesman criticised this decision claiming that it was driven by the governments attempt to bring the budget into surplus and reducing the levy would provide a boost to the economy in the  budget collins announced a  billion cut in acc levies over the next two years collins said the earners and workers accounts were now fully funded after the corporation reduced the number of long term acc claimants from  to less than  in  acc’s outstanding claims liability ocl increased by  billion which lead to a net deficit of  billion the ocl measures the future cost of all existing acc claims that year also saw  million claims accepted a  increase from the previous year  billion was paid out to all new and existing claims there has been some conjecture over whether or not acc staff were paid incentives to remove long term clients off weekly compensation this was refuted by exceo ralph stewart in  that year there were  longterm claimants registered with acc – down by over  notable eventsedit violence against staffedit in some cases acc clients have threatened or attempted to harm acc staff members in  a staff member was fatally stabbed by a claimant at an acc office in henderson in  acc logos were removed from company vehicles after several staff were rammed or driven off the road by other drivers the following year a threat against former chief executive ralph stewart led to a decision for security staff to be posted outside his home there have been at least two threats to blow up a car bomb outside acc offices and police have had to be called on several other occasions in  there were a total of  recorded threats made against staff  the majority against case managers making difficult decisions on clients cases client fraudedit in  it was reported that  people have been convicted of defrauding acc of a total of more than  million over the past four years this includes clients claiming they were injured but who kept working while receiving acc benefits and medical practitioners who billed acc for more treatment than they actually provided another category of acc fraudster includes widows who continued claiming payments after their injured partners have subsequently died sometimes these payments went on for nearly  years before the fraud came to light – with one woman receiving nearly  after her husband had died staff fraudedit there have been a number of cases where acc staff have defrauded the corporation jeffrey chapman former acc chief executive from  to  was imprisoned for defrauding acc and other government agencies gavin robbins his successor from  to  was also charged with fraud but was acquitted in  a senior manager was convicted of dishonesty offences involving property leased to acc by private business interests in late  jonathan wright an acccontracted medical assessor was convicted of dishonestly obtaining over  in falsified travel expenses from acc treatment injury claimsedit medical misadventure claims were relabelled as treatment injury claims ti in  a treatment injury is when an injury is caused by treatment provided by a registered health professional these injuries are not a necessary part or ordinary consequence of the treatment bronwyn pullar privacy breachedit acc has had a number of breaches of privacy relating to claimants the most significant occurred in  after the release of details of  claimants to an acc claimant bronwyn pullar pullar had been battling acc since suffering a head injury in —and had  separate complaints against the agency—only one of which was about the privacy breaches in  she and former national party president michelle boag had a meeting with two senior acc managers to discuss her concerns acc referred the matter to the police claiming pullar had threatened to go to the media about the privacy breaches if she didnt get what she wanted the police listened to a tape recording of the meeting and decided there was no case to answer in march  acc minister nick smith resigned from cabinet after it was revealed that he had written letters on behalf of pullar who was a personal friend of his while he was acc minister acc chairman john judge continued to insist his version of events was correct and as a result acc minister judith collins did not renew his tenure on the acc board the chief executive of acc ralph stewart also resigned the next day three other board members – murray hilder rob campbell and john mccliskie – also resigned the fallout from the affair continued in may  when collins sued labour mps trevor mallard and andrew little for defamation over comments they made on radio new zealand broadcasts linking her to the leak of an email from michelle boag following the release of the files the case was settled after a high court hearing in november  an independent review of acc was conducted towards the end of  and found the organisation lacked a comprehensive strategy for protecting and managing claimants information and said acc had an almost cavalier attitude toward its clients the review showed that the culture within acc enabled its staff to target clients involved in privacy breaches and complaints rather than demonstrating respect for claimants in  a training academy for staff was mooted with an emphasis on a clientcentred approach see alsoedit tort reform atiyahs accidents referencesedit  accident compensation act   new zealand legislation parliamentary counsel office   see donselaar v donselaar   nzlr  confirmed by auckland city council v blundell   nzlr   nz rugby foundation  rugby smart wwwsportyconz retrieved    about » ride forever retrieved    preventing sexual violence wwwaccconz retrieved    make your home a safety zone wwwsafekidsnz retrieved    annual report  of the accident compensation commission p  see fenton v thorley  wn  for an old definition  a b how were funded  acc retrieved  may    current year’s levy rates acc  august  retrieved  february    a b types of cover for selfemployed wwwaccconz retrieved    a b the painful bills about to wallop your wallet  physiotherapy claims summary  acc moves to curtail rise in physiotherapy costs archived february   at the wayback machine  armstrong grahame  october  the painful bills about to wallop your wallet the sunday star times retrieved  may  dead link  funding issue brews in accs cauldron  govt ignored ministry call to trim acc levies by m  acc leads good economic news at national party convention nz herald  may   accs outstanding claims liability wwwaccconz retrieved    exboss defends acc rehabilitation policy    acc staff in line of fire  acc frauds hit m over past four years  don rennie administering accident compensation in the s   vuwlr  