e been a number of cases where acc staff have defrauded the corporation jeffrey chapman former acc chief executive from  to  was imprisoned for defrauding acc and other government agencies gavin robbins his successor from  to  was also charged with fraud but was acquitted in  a senior manager was convicted of dishonesty offences involving property leased to acc by private business interests in late  jonathan wright an acccontracted medical assessor was convicted of dishonestly obtaining over  in falsified travel expenses from acc treatment injury claimsedit medical misadventure claims were relabelled as treatment injury claims ti in  a treatment injury is when an injury is caused by treatment provided by a registered health professional these injuries are not a necessary part or ordinary consequence of the treatment bronwyn pullar privacy breachedit acc has had a number of breaches of privacy relating to claimants the most significant occurred in  after the release of details of  claimants to an acc claimant bronwyn pullar pullar had been battling acc since suffering a head injury in —and had  separate complaints against the agency—only one of which was about the privacy breaches in  she and former national party president michelle boag had a meeting with two senior acc managers to discuss her concerns acc referred the matter to the police claiming pullar had threatened to go to the media about the privacy breaches if she didnt get what she wanted the police listened to a tape recording of the meeting and decided there was no case to answer in march  acc minister nick smith resigned from cabinet after it was revealed that he had written letters on behalf of pullar who was a personal friend of his while he was acc minister acc chairman john judge continued to insist his version of events was correct and as a result acc minister judith collins did not renew his tenure on the acc board the chief executive of acc ralph stewart also resigned the next day three other board members – murray hilder rob campbell and john mccliskie – also resigned the fallout from the affair continued in may  when collins sued labour mps trevor mallard and andrew little for defamation over comments they made on radio new zealand broadcasts linking her to the leak of an email from michelle boag following the release of the files the case was settled after a high court hearing in november  an independent review of acc was conducted towards the end of  and found the organisation lacked a comprehensive strategy for protecting and managing claimants information and said acc had an almost cavalier attitude toward its clients the review showed that the culture within acc enabled its staff to target clients involved in privacy breaches and complaints rather than demonstrating respect for claimants in  a training academy for staff was mooted with an emphasis on a clientcentred approach see alsoedit tort reform atiyahs accidents referencesedit  accident compensation act   new zealand legislation parliamentary counsel office   see donselaar v donselaar   nzlr  confirmed by auckland city council v blundell   nzlr   nz rugby foundation  rugby smart wwwsportyconz retrieved    about » ride forever retrieved    preventing sexual violence wwwaccconz retrieved    make your home a safety zone wwwsafekidsnz retrieved    annual report  of the accident compensation commission p  see fenton v thorley  wn  for an old definition  a b how were funded  acc retrieved  may    current year’s levy rates acc  august  retrieved  february    a b types of cover for selfemployed wwwaccconz retrieved    a b the painful bills about to wallop your wallet  physiotherapy claims summary  acc moves to curtail rise in physiotherapy costs archived february   at the wayback machine  armstrong grahame  october  the painful bills about to wallop your wallet the sunday star times retrieved  may  dead link  funding issue brews in accs cauldron  govt ignored ministry call to trim acc levies by m  acc le