as a personal friend of his while he was acc minister acc chairman john judge continued to insist his version of events was correct and as a result acc minister judith collins did not renew his tenure on the acc board the chief executive of acc ralph stewart also resigned the next day three other board members – murray hilder rob campbell and john mccliskie – also resigned the fallout from the affair continued in may  when collins sued labour mps trevor mallard and andrew little for defamation over comments they made on radio new zealand broadcasts linking her to the leak of an email from michelle boag following the release of the files the case was settled after a high court hearing in november  an independent review of acc was conducted towards the end of  and found the organisation lacked a comprehensive strategy for protecting and managing claimants information and said acc had an almost cavalier attitude toward its clients the review showed that the culture within acc enabled its staff to target clients involved in privacy breaches and complaints rather than demonstrating respect for claimants in  a training academy for staff was mooted with an emphasis on a clientcentred approach see alsoedit tort reform atiyahs accidents referencesedit  accident compensation act   new zealand legislation parliamentary counsel office   see donselaar v donselaar   nzlr  confirmed by auckland city council v blundell   nzlr   nz rugby foundation  rugby smart wwwsportyconz retrieved    about » ride forever retrieved    preventing sexual violence wwwaccconz retrieved    make your home a safety zone wwwsafekidsnz retrieved    annual report  of the accident compensation commission p  see fenton v thorley  wn  for an old definition  a b how were funded  acc retrieved  may    current year’s levy rates acc  august  retrieved  february    a b types of cover for selfemployed wwwaccconz retrieved    a b the painful bills about to wallop your wallet  physiotherapy claims summary  acc moves 